title.narrative: Output 2.2: Strengthened leadership, commitment, accountability and capacity for evidence-based equity-focused planning and budgeting for scale-up of HIV and AIDS prevention and treatment interventions for children and adolescent girls and boys.

description.narrative:
UNICEF contributed technically and financially toward strengthening leadership, commitment, accountability and capacity for evidence-based equity-focused planning and budgeting for scale-up of HIV and AIDS prevention and treatment interventions for children and adolescent girls and boys and achieved all the three indicators on strengthening multisectoral coordination mechanisms with seven out of a target of two being functional. UNICEF strengthened the availability of gender-responsive evidence for the All-In framework for prevention of HIV, which was adopted/applied in subsequent programme design and implementation, and ensured quarterly availability of age-disaggregated data on HIV for all districts through the national management information system.
| Status:On-track | As-of Date:14/01/2020
